  "description": "Atlassian Design System is the token-driven color system behind Jira, Confluence and Trello. It is a reference for step-for-purpose at enterprise scale: a base 100-1000 palette plus a large semantic token layer where every token ships with its own usage description.",
  "philosophy": "Base ramps run 100-1000 with extra 250 and 850 steps inserted purely for pressed states (subtlest chain 100/200/250, bold chain 700/800/850). The chromatic ramps are theme-invariant; dark mode is achieved by remapping which step a semantic token uses, roughly mirroring around the middle (brand bold is Blue700 in light, Blue400 in dark; subtlest backgrounds swap 100 for 1000). Only the neutral axis gets a second hand-tuned ramp: light Neutral 0-1200 pairs with a separate DarkNeutral ramp (never an inversion), and both come with alpha variants (Neutral100A-500A) so layered UI adapts to elevation. Color reaches products only through role.emphasis.state tokens (e.g. color.background.danger.bold.hovered) tuned to WCAG AA: border.bold guarantees 3:1, text steps 700/800/1000 give subtlest/subtle/default text.",
