  "solidForeground": "white in both themes for brand/danger/success bold (color.text.inverse = Neutral0 light / DarkNeutral100 dark); warning.bold is Orange300 and uses dark text via color.text.warning.inverse (Neutral1000)",
  "notes": "Semantic roles per the tokens themselves: success is the Lime ramp and warning the Orange ramp (Green and Yellow still exist but only as meaning-free accent colors since the brand refresh). Chromatic ramps are shared by both themes, so dark equals light for them; dark mode instead remaps steps (bold 700->400, subtle 100->1000, borders 600->500) - only the neutral scale has a real dark ramp (DarkNeutral). Neutral steps are paired by number (Neutral X / DarkNeutral X), which matches mid-ramp token pairs (text.subtle 800/800, border.bold 600/600) but shifts at the extremes: elevation.surface is Neutral0 light yet DarkNeutral100 dark. Omitted here: Neutral1200 (#000000) / DarkNeutral1200 (#FFFFFF) and DarkNeutral -100/250/350 (extra dark-only surface steps), plus the alpha variants Neutral100A-500A / DarkNeutral-100A-500A used for color.background.neutral (Neutral200A), color.border (Neutral300A) and disabled states - so uiBg/uiBgHover/uiBgActive/border in roleMapping point at the solid analogs of those alpha steps. The neutral scale keeps its own step names (0-1100), one step offset from the chromatic 100-1000 names in stepNames. solid=7 (X700) holds for brand/danger/success; warning.bold is the documented exception at Orange300/400. Neutral solid (background.neutral.bold) is Neutral1000, index 10."
